---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "How to Check BC PNP Application Status & Update Your Profile 2026";
const description =
    "Step-by-step guide to creating your BC PNP profile, checking application status, and updating your SIRS registration. Learn how to use BCPNP Online portal effectively.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
    <article class="min-h-screen bg-slate-50 py-12 px-4 sm:px-6">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-8">
            <header class="space-y-4 text-center">
                <div
                    class="inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-bold mb-4"
                >
                    Step-by-Step Guide
                </div>
                <h1
                    class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight leading-tight"
                >
                    BC PNP Profile & <span class="text-blue-600">Status Guide</span>
                </h1>
                <p
                    class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed"
                >
                    Everything you need to know about creating, checking, and updating your BC PNP profile through the BCPNP Online portal.
                </p>
            </header>

            <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                <div
                    class="bg-white border border-slate-200 p-5 rounded-2xl text-center"
                >
                    <div class="text-3xl font-black text-blue-600 mb-2">12 mo</div>
                    <div class="text-sm text-slate-600 font-medium">
                        Profile Validity
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div
                    class="bg-white border border-slate-200 p-5 rounded-2xl text-center"
                >
                    <div class="text-3xl font-black text-green-600 mb-2">30 days</div>
                    <div class="text-sm text-slate-600 font-medium">
                        To Submit After ITA
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div
                    class="bg-white border border-slate-200 p-5 rounded-2xl text-center"
                >
                    <div class="text-3xl font-black text-purple-600 mb-2">24/7</div>
                    <div class="text-sm text-slate-600 font-medium">
                        Portal Access
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="prose prose-lg prose-slate max-w-none bg-white p-8 sm:p-12 rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-sm"
            >
                <h2>How to Create a BC PNP Profile</h2>
                <p>
                    Before you can be considered for a BC PNP invitation, you must create a profile in the <strong>Skills Immigration Registration System (SIRS)</strong> through the BCPNP Online portal.
                </p>

                <h3>Step 1: Access BCPNP Online</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Go to <a href="https://www.pnpapplication.gov.bc.ca/" rel="nofollow">pnpapplication.gov.bc.ca</a></li>
                    <li>Click "Register" to create a new account</li>
                    <li>Enter your email address and create a password</li>
                    <li>Verify your email through the confirmation link</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-400 p-5 rounded-r-xl my-6 not-prose">
                    <p class="font-bold text-amber-900 mb-1">Important</p>
                    <p class="text-amber-800 text-sm">
                        Use an email you check regularly. All official communications, including invitations to apply (ITAs), are sent to this email. Check your spam folder too.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h3>Step 2: Complete Your Profile</h3>
                <p>You'll need to provide information in these categories:</p>

                <div class="not-prose space-y-3 my-6">
                    <div class="flex items-start bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
                        <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-bold mr-4">1</span>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Personal Information</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Name, date of birth, country of citizenship, current immigration status in Canada</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-start bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
                        <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-bold mr-4">2</span>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Job Offer Details</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Employer name, NOC code, job title, hourly wage, work location, job duties</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-start bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
                        <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-bold mr-4">3</span>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Work Experience</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Employment history with dates, job titles, hours worked, and relevance to your job offer</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-start bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
                        <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-bold mr-4">4</span>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Education</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Highest credential, institution name, country, completion date</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-start bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
                        <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-bold mr-4">5</span>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Language Test Results</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">IELTS, CELPIP, or TEF scores (if applicable to your stream)</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3>Step 3: Review and Submit</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Review all sections for accuracy</li>
                    <li>Ensure your NOC code matches your actual job duties</li>
                    <li>Verify your wage is stated as hourly rate (not annual)</li>
                    <li>Submit your registration</li>
                    <li>You'll receive a confirmation with your <strong>registration number</strong></li>
                </ol>

                <div class="bg-green-50 p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-200 my-6 not-prose">
                    <p class="font-bold text-green-900 mb-1">Your SIRS Score</p>
                    <p class="text-green-800 text-sm">
                        After submission, the system calculates your score (out of 200 points). You can see this score in your profile. Use our <a href="/bc-pnp-calculator" class="text-green-700 underline">BC PNP Calculator</a> to verify it matches.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h2>How to Check BC PNP Application Status</h2>
                <p>
                    There are two types of "status" you might be checking:
                </p>

                <h3>1. SIRS Registration Status (Pre-ITA)</h3>
                <p>
                    If you've registered but haven't received an Invitation to Apply yet:
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Log in to <a href="https://www.pnpapplication.gov.bc.ca/" rel="nofollow">BCPNP Online</a></li>
                    <li>Go to "My Registrations"</li>
                    <li>Check your status—it will show one of these:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Active:</strong> In the pool, waiting for invitation</li>
                            <li><strong>Invited:</strong> You received an ITA</li>
                            <li><strong>Expired:</strong> 12 months passed without invitation</li>
                            <li><strong>Withdrawn:</strong> You cancelled your registration</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>

                <h3>2. Application Status (Post-ITA)</h3>
                <p>
                    If you've submitted a full application after receiving an ITA:
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Log in to BCPNP Online</li>
                    <li>Go to "My Applications"</li>
                    <li>Click on your application to see detailed status</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="not-prose overflow-x-auto my-6">
                    <table class="min-w-full text-left text-sm">
                        <thead class="bg-slate-50 border-b border-slate-200">
                            <tr>
                                <th class="px-4 py-3 font-bold">Status</th>
                                <th class="px-4 py-3 font-bold">What It Means</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Submitted</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">Application received, awaiting review</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Under Review</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">Officer is actively reviewing your file</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Additional Documents Requested</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">You need to submit more documents</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Decision Made</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">Check for approval or refusal letter</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-green-50">
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-green-700">Approved</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-700">Nomination certificate issued</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-red-50">
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-red-700">Refused</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-red-700">Application denied (see refusal letter)</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h2>Can I Update My BC PNP Profile?</h2>
                <p>
                    <strong>Yes, but with important restrictions.</strong> Your ability to update depends on your current stage:
                </p>

                <h3>Before Receiving an ITA</h3>
                <p>
                    While your registration is active in the SIRS pool, you <strong>can update</strong>:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Contact information (email, phone, address)</li>
                    <li>Job offer details (if you get a new job or raise)</li>
                    <li>Language test scores (if you retake the test)</li>
                    <li>Work experience (as you gain more)</li>
                    <li>Education (if you complete a new credential)</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="bg-blue-50 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-200 my-6 not-prose">
                    <p class="font-bold text-blue-900 mb-1">Pro Tip: Update Strategically</p>
                    <p class="text-blue-800 text-sm">
                        Every time you update your profile, your score is recalculated. If you improve your language score or get a higher-paying job, update immediately to increase your chances in the next draw.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h3>After Receiving an ITA</h3>
                <p>
                    Once you receive an Invitation to Apply, <strong>you cannot change</strong> the information that was in your registration at the time of invitation. Your full application must match your registration.
                </p>

                <p>
                    If your circumstances change after an ITA (e.g., job loss, new employer), you must:
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Contact BC PNP immediately</li>
                    <li>Disclose the change in your application</li>
                    <li>The change may result in your application being refused if you no longer qualify</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>After Submitting Full Application</h3>
                <p>
                    After submission, you generally <strong>cannot make changes</strong> unless:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>BC PNP requests additional documents</li>
                    <li>You need to correct an error (contact BC PNP)</li>
                    <li>Your circumstances change materially (must report)</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>How to Update Your BC PNP Profile</h2>
                <p>Follow these steps to update your SIRS registration:</p>

                <div class="not-prose space-y-3 my-6">
                    <div class="flex items-start bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
                        <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-bold mr-4">1</span>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Log In</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Access BCPNP Online at pnpapplication.gov.bc.ca</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-start bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
                        <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-bold mr-4">2</span>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Go to My Registrations</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Find your active SIRS registration</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-start bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
                        <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-bold mr-4">3</span>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Click "Edit Registration"</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">This unlocks the form for editing</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-start bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
                        <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-bold mr-4">4</span>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Make Your Changes</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Update the relevant sections with new information</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-start bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
                        <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-bold mr-4">5</span>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900">Review and Submit</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Double-check accuracy, then submit the updated registration</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-5 rounded-r-xl my-6 not-prose">
                    <p class="font-bold text-red-900 mb-1">Warning: Be Honest</p>
                    <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">
                        All information must be accurate and verifiable. Misrepresentation can result in a 2-year ban from all Canadian immigration programs. Don't inflate your wage, experience, or education.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h2>Common Profile Issues and Solutions</h2>

                <h3>Issue: My Score Dropped After Updating</h3>
                <p>
                    This can happen if:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>You corrected an error that was inflating your score</li>
                    <li>Your language test expired (scores reset to 0)</li>
                    <li>You changed jobs to a lower-paying position</li>
                    <li>BC PNP updated the scoring formula</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Issue: I Can't Edit My Registration</h3>
                <p>
                    This happens when:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>You already received an ITA (cannot edit)</li>
                    <li>Your registration expired (must create new one)</li>
                    <li>System maintenance is ongoing (try later)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Issue: My Registration Expired</h3>
                <p>
                    SIRS registrations are valid for <strong>12 months</strong>. If you weren't invited within that time, you must create a new registration. Your old information is not carried over automatically.
                </p>

                <h2>Processing Time Tracking</h2>
                <p>
                    Current BC PNP processing times (as of January 2026):
                </p>

                <div class="not-prose overflow-x-auto my-6">
                    <table class="min-w-full text-left text-sm">
                        <thead class="bg-blue-50 border-b border-blue-200">
                            <tr>
                                <th class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-blue-900">Stage</th>
                                <th class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-blue-900">Typical Timeline</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">SIRS Registration to ITA</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">Varies (depends on draws)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">Application Review (Standard)</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">2-3 months</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">Application Review (Tech)</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">2-4 weeks</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">Nomination to PR (Express Entry)</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">~6 months</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">Nomination to PR (Non-EE)</td>
                                <td class="px-4 py-3">12-18 months</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <p>
                    For detailed processing times, see our <a href="/articles/bc-pnp-processing-times">BC PNP Processing Times guide</a>.
                </p>

                <div class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-green-200 mt-8 not-prose">
                    <p class="font-bold text-green-900 mb-2">Calculate Your Score Before Registering</p>
                    <p class="text-green-800 text-sm mb-4">
                        Know your score before you create a profile. This helps you decide if you should apply now or work on improving your profile first.
                    </p>
                    <a href="/bc-pnp-calculator" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-bold transition-colors">
                        Calculate Your Score →
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-sm">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-slate-900 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <details class="group bg-slate-50 p-5 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 open:bg-white open:ring-1 open:ring-blue-100 open:shadow-md transition-all">
                        <summary class="font-bold text-slate-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
                            <span>How often should I check my BC PNP status?</span>
                            <span class="transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180 text-blue-500">▼</span>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="mt-4 text-slate-600 text-sm border-t border-slate-100 pt-4">
                            For SIRS registrations, checking once a week is enough—draws typically happen weekly when active, and you'll receive an email if invited. For submitted applications, check every 1-2 weeks unless you're expecting a document request.
                        </div>
                    </details>

                    <details class="group bg-slate-50 p-5 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 open:bg-white open:ring-1 open:ring-blue-100 open:shadow-md transition-all">
                        <summary class="font-bold text-slate-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
                            <span>Can I have multiple BC PNP registrations?</span>
                            <span class="transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180 text-blue-500">▼</span>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="mt-4 text-slate-600 text-sm border-t border-slate-100 pt-4">
                            No, you can only have one active SIRS registration at a time. If you want to change streams (e.g., from Skilled Worker to International Graduate), you must withdraw your existing registration first, then create a new one.
                        </div>
                    </details>

                    <details class="group bg-slate-50 p-5 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 open:bg-white open:ring-1 open:ring-blue-100 open:shadow-md transition-all">
                        <summary class="font-bold text-slate-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
                            <span>What happens if I miss the 30-day deadline after ITA?</span>
                            <span class="transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180 text-blue-500">▼</span>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="mt-4 text-slate-600 text-sm border-t border-slate-100 pt-4">
                            If you don't submit your full application within 30 days of receiving an ITA, your invitation expires. You can re-register in SIRS, but you'll have to wait for another draw. There's no extension available.
                        </div>
                    </details>

                    <details class="group bg-slate-50 p-5 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 open:bg-white open:ring-1 open:ring-blue-100 open:shadow-md transition-all">
                        <summary class="font-bold text-slate-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
                            <span>Can I contact BC PNP about my application status?</span>
                            <span class="transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180 text-blue-500">▼</span>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="mt-4 text-slate-600 text-sm border-t border-slate-100 pt-4">
                            Yes, but only if your application has exceeded normal processing times. Contact them through the BCPNP Online portal messaging system. General status inquiries for applications within normal timelines typically won't receive a response.
                        </div>
                    </details>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <a href="/articles/bc-pnp-eligibility-requirements-2026" class="block bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
                    <span class="text-xs font-bold text-blue-600 uppercase tracking-wider">Related Guide</span>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mt-2">Am I Eligible for BC PNP?</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">Check if you meet the requirements before creating your profile.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="/articles/bc-pnp-documents-checklist" class="block bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
                    <span class="text-xs font-bold text-blue-600 uppercase tracking-wider">Related Guide</span>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mt-2">BC PNP Documents Checklist</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">Get all your documents ready before you receive an ITA.</p>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>
